Business Brief -- Electronic Arts:
   Fiscal 3rd-Quarter's Profit
   Rose 74%; Stock Fell $1.25
Yesterday, in national over-the-counter trading,
Electronic Arts closed at $44, down $1.25.
   The video-game maker, based in San Mateo, Calif., said
sales of its video-game software for Sega, Genesis and Super
Nintendo Entertainment systems boomed in the U.S., Europe and
Australia.
   For the nine months, the net income spurted 60% to $11
million, or $1.03 a share, from $6.8 million, or 65 cents a
share, a year earlier. Revenue increased 50% to $116.7
million from $78.3 million a year earlier.